3.100. 
Grounds for the termination of the community property The community property shall be terminated on the following grounds:
1) the death of one of the spouses; 
2) the declaration of the death of one of the spouses or his/her unknown whereabouts; 
3) the annulment of the marriage; 
4) the dissolution of the marriage; 
5) the separation of the spouses; 
6) the division of the community property by a court decision; 
7) the change of the legal regime of the property by agreement of the spouses; 
8) any other cases provided for by law.
